"由圆环病毒引起的致死性传染病，主要影响羽毛和喙部。病毒攻击羽毛毛囊、喙和爪基质，导致进行性羽毛、爪和喙的畸形和坏死。多见于3岁以下幼鸟，目前无法治愈。" = "A fatal infectious disease caused by circovirus, which mainly affects feathers and beaks. The virus attacks the feather follicles, beak, and claw matrix, causing progressive deformity and necrosis of the feathers, claws, and beak. It is more common in young birds under 3 years old and there is currently no cure.";
"由巨型酵母菌(Macrorhabdus ornithogaster)引起的消化道疾病，主要影响腺胃。常见于虎皮鹦鹉、玄凤和金丝雀。可导致慢性消瘦。" = "Digestive tract disease caused by Macrorhabdus ornithogaster, mainly affecting the glandular stomach. Commonly seen in budgies, blackbirds and canaries. Can lead to chronic weight loss.";
"由球虫（艾美耳球虫）引起的肠道寄生虫病，主要通过粪便-口腔途径传播。幼鸟和免疫力低下的鸟更易感染，可导致严重腹泻和死亡。" = "Intestinal parasitic diseases caused by coccidia (Eimeria), mainly transmitted through the fecal-oral route. Young and immunocompromised birds are more susceptible to infection, which can cause severe diarrhea and death.";
"由疥螨(Knemidokoptes)引起，主要侵害喙部、蜡膜、眼周和脚部。形成灰白色蜂窝状或海绵状痂皮，严重时导致喙部变形。常见于虎皮鹦鹉。" = "Caused by scabies mites (Knemidokoptes), it mainly attacks the beak, wax membrane, around the eyes and feet. Gray-white honeycomb or spongy scabs form, which can lead to deformation of the beak in severe cases. Commonly seen in budgies.";
"由禽分枝杆菌引起的慢性消耗性疾病，病程长，治疗困难。主要影响消化系统，导致慢性消瘦。有潜在的人畜共患风险。" = "Chronic wasting disease caused by Mycobacterium avium has a long course and is difficult to treat. Mainly affects the digestive system, leading to chronic weight loss. There is a potential zoonotic risk.";
"由贾第鞭毛虫引起的肠道寄生虫病，可导致皮肤瘙痒、羽毛问题和腹泻。此病为人畜共患病，可通过污染的水源传播给人。" = "An intestinal parasitic disease caused by Giardia that can cause itchy skin, feather problems and diarrhea. This disease is a zoonotic disease and can be transmitted to humans through contaminated water sources.";
"由鹦鹉热衣原体引起的人畜共患病，可传染给人类。病鸟可能长期带菌排毒。人感染后出现类似流感的症状，严重可致肺炎。养鸟者需特别注意防护。" = "A zoonotic disease caused by Chlamydia psittaci that can be transmitted to humans. Sick birds may carry bacteria and shed viruses for a long time. People develop flu-like symptoms after infection, which can lead to pneumonia in severe cases. Bird keepers need to pay special attention to protection.";
