"鸟儿羽毛持续蓬松、炸毛，看起来像个毛球。这是鸟类身体不适的重要信号，通过蓬松羽毛来保持体温。健康的鸟只有在休息或睡觉时才会短暂蓬松羽毛。" = "The bird's feathers continue to become fluffy and puffy, looking like a ball of hair. This is an important sign that the bird is not feeling well and uses fluffy feathers to maintain body temperature. Healthy birds only fluff their feathers briefly when resting or sleeping.";
"鸟儿进食量明显减少或完全不吃东西。由于鸟类新陈代谢快，24小时不进食可能危及生命。食欲下降往往是多种疾病的早期信号。" = "The bird eats significantly less or doesn't eat at all. Because birds have fast metabolisms, not eating for 24 hours can be life-threatening. Decreased appetite is often an early sign of many diseases.";
"鸟儿频繁啄自己或同伴的羽毛，导致羽毛脱落、皮肤裸露甚至出血。这是一种复杂的行为问题，可能由生理或心理因素引起。" = "Birds frequently peck their own or their companions' feathers, causing feathers to fall off, skin to be exposed, and even bleeding. It is a complex behavioral problem that may be caused by physical or psychological factors.";
"鸟儿频繁甩头并吐出食物或粘液。需区分正常的求偶喂食行为和病理性呕吐。病理性呕吐通常伴随精神萎靡，呕吐物可能有异味。" = "The bird frequently shakes its head and spits out food or mucus. It is necessary to distinguish between normal courtship and feeding behavior and pathological vomiting. Pathological vomiting is usually accompanied by listlessness, and the vomitus may have a peculiar smell.";
